result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyrell Jamar Cowans Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Trespass to Dwelling, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.14.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

AS TO COUNT 1:

Court sentences defendant to serve 135 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 135 (one hundred thirty-five) days, a TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

Court will waive non-mandatory costs and surcharges.

Court ordrered mandatory surcharges due by January 25, 2016 or entry of a civil judgment.

Court ordered DNA sample after today's proceedings.

Defendant Tyrell Jamar Cowans in court with attorney Colin P. McGinn.  Kelly O'Neill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: TC. Court ordered stayed warrant lifted.

A STO COUNT 1:

Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the criminal complaint and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.

Attorney Colin P. McGinn in court.  Kelly O'Neill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a bench warrant issued but stayed the issuance until the next scheduled hearing.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for November 24, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the state via-telephone: Dr. Adrea McGlynn. Testimony closed. Closing arguments by state and defense. Arguments heard as to bail.

For reasons stated on the record, State and Court adopts Dr. Adrea McGynn's findings. The court finds the defendant not competent to proceed but likely to become competent within the statutory time period.  if provided with appropriate treatment, is likely to become competent within 12 months or within the maximum sentence specified for the most serious offense, whichever is less.  The court orders the proceedings remains suspended and continues committment of the defendant to the Department of Health Services (Mendota) for an indeterminate term not to exceed 12 months, or the maximum sentence specified for the most serious offense, whichever is less.  Court ordered case adjourned for review hearing in Branch 37.  Review hearing scheduled for December 1, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Tyrell Jamar Cowans in court with attorney Colin P. McGinn.  Defendant Tyrell Jamar Cowans in custody.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: TC.

Competency hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the state via-telephone:  Dr. Deborah Collins, Director of Wisconsin Forensic Unit. State and defense rest.  Testimony closed.  Closing arguments by state and defense. Court finds based on Dr. Collins examination defendant incompetent to proceed at this time but is likely to become competent.  Court found the defendant is not competent to refuse psychotropic medication or treatment due to mental illness because the defendant is incapable of expressing an understanding of the advantages and disadvantages of accepting psychotropic medication or treatment and adopts findings.   Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Department of Health Services.  Court ordered case adjourned for review hearing in Branch 37. Order for Treatment; signed and filed.  Review hearing scheduled for September 1, 2015 at 08:30 am.
